'''Tyler Robert Fletcher''' (born 19 March 2007) is a professional footballer who plays as a [[Midfield (association football)|midfielder]] for [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and the [[Scotland national football team|Scotland national team]].

He joined [[Manchester United F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Manchester United's youth system]] in 2023, from [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. He made his first-team debut for United in February 2026. Fletcher is the son of [[Darren Fletcher]] and the twin brother of [[Jack Fletcher (footballer, born 2007)|Jack Fletcher]]. He has represented both England and Scotland at youth international level. He made his senior international debut for Scotland in May 2026 and was also named as a late replacement in their [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] squad.

==Club career==
Fletcher, and his twin brother Jack, were part of the academy at [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for nine years prior to agreeing to sign for [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] for a combined fee of £1.25 million in July 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-united-jack-tyler-fletcher-27376941.amp|website=Manchester Evening News|title=Manchester United agree fee for Jack and Tyler Fletcher from Man City|first=Samuel|last=Luckhurst|accessdate=23 July 2023|date=22 July 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/38054391/manchester-united-signing-darren-fletcher-twin-sons-city-sources|last=Dawson|first=Rob|website=espn|accessdate=23 July 2023|title= Man United signing Fletcher's twin sons from City - sources|date=22 July 2023}}</ref> He signed his first professional contract with the club in April 2024, shortly after his 17th birthday.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.mayonews.ie/news/home/1467478/twin-sons-of-man-utd-legend-and-grandsons-of-achill-woman-sign-man-utd-contracts.html|website=Mayo News|accessdate=4 April 2024|title= Twin sons of Man Utd legend and grandsons of Achill woman sign Man Utd contracts|first=Anton|last=McNulty|date=4 April 2024}}</ref>

Fletcher made his [[Premier League]] debut as a second half substitute in a 2–0 home win against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 7 February 2026.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/what-michael-carrick-told-tyler-33385281.amp |website=Manchester Evening News|accessdate=10 February 2026|title= What Michael Carrick told Tyler Fletcher to do during his Man United debut vs Tottenham|date=8 Feb 2026|first=Jack|last=Flintham}}</ref> With his brother Jack also making his debut for the club that season, it marked the first time that a set of twins and their father had all played in the English top flight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/detail/the-fletcher-family-make-top-flight-football-history-in-england|website=Manutd.com|accessdate=10 February 2026|title=Fletchers are a footballing first|first=Adam|last=Marshall|date=10 February 2026}}</ref> In May 2026, he won the [[Manchester United F.C. Under-21s and Academy#Players of the Year|Denzil Haroun Reserve Team Player of the Year]] award.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.manutd.com/en/news/tyler-fletcher-awarded-the-denzil-haroun-trophy-2025-26 |website=manutd.com |title=
Tyler Fletcher awarded the Denzil Haroun trophy |date=15 May 2026 |access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Fletcher is eligible to represent England, Scotland, and the Republic of Ireland at international level.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cx2nwd7vn2no |website=BBC Sport |title=Fletcher twins in England-Scotland U19 clash |date=17 November 2025 |access-date=30 May 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.balls.ie/football/manchester-uniteds-darren-fletcher-mayo-links-647119 |website=balls.ie |title=Manchester United's New Interim Manager Has Very Strong Mayo Links |date=5 January 2026 |access-date=30 May 2026}}</ref> He has represented England at [[England national under-16 football team|under-16]] level, and Scotland at [[Scotland national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[Scotland national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[Scotland national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[Scotland national under-19 football team|under-19]], [[Scotland national under-21 football team|under-21]] and [[Scotland national football team|senior]] levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe901209/tyler-fletcher/international-matches/ |website=worldfootball.net |title=Tyler Fletcher Statistics International Matches |access-date=30 May 2026}}</ref>

He played for both England and Scotland at under-16 level, representing Scotland as his father did, and England, as his brother Jack did.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talksport.com/football/1508369/man-united-darren-fletcher-sons-man-city-tyler-jack-transfer/|website=Talksport|accessdate=23 July 2023|title= Manchester United to sign Darren Fletcher's sons from Man City in British record deals for U16 players|first=Natasha|last=Everitt|date=22 July 2023}}</ref> In October 2023, he confirmed his decision to represent Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|website=Manchester Evening News|accessdate=23 October 2023|url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-united-news-tyler-fletcher-27962482.amp|date=23 October 2023|first=Samuel|last=Luckhurst|title=Manchester United youngster Tyler Fletcher switches back to Scotland after England stint}}</ref> In 2025, he captained Scotland at under-18 level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/amp/fletcher-twins-make-history-as-captains-of-scotland-and-england-u-18s-1353162|title=Fletcher twins make history as captains of Scotland and England U-18s}}</ref> He was included in the Scotland under-21 squad for the first time in March 2026.<ref>{{cite web |title=Manchester United's Tyler Fletcher earns first Scotland U21 call |website=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cz6eq5e5169o |access-date=17 March 2026 |date=17 March 2026}}</ref> 

Fletcher was one of four young players invited to train with the Scotland squad ahead of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cgepznz1xe8o |title=Scotland call up James Wilson, Liam McFarlane, Luke Graham and Tyler Fletcher for pre-World Cup training |website=BBC Sport |date=20 May 2026 |accessdate=21 May 2026}}</ref> and he made his senior international debut in a friendly against [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] on 30 May 2026.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c87qqyvp508t |title=International Friendly LIVE: Scotland vs Curacao: score, report, clips, text updates, reaction & match stats |website=BBC Sport |quote=Tyler Fletcher - son of former Manchester United and Scotland midfielder Darren - came on for his debut after the break, and [[Lawrence Shankland|Shankland]] struck twice to advance his case for a starting berth at the World Cup. |date=30 May 2026 |accessdate=30 May 2026 |first=Andy |last=Burke}}</ref> [[Billy Gilmour]] suffered a knee injury during the game, ruling him out of the tournament, with Fletcher being announced as his replacement the following day.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn8pmj99jk7o |title=Fletcher chosen to replace Gilmour in Scotland squad |website=BBC Sport |date=31 May 2026 |accessdate=31 May 2026}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the son of [[Darren Fletcher]] and the twin brother of professional footballer [[Jack Fletcher (footballer, born 2007)|Jack Fletcher]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportsgazette.co.uk/fletcher-brothers-shine-in-fa-youth-cup-as-scotland-fans-hope-for-the-best/|title=Fletcher Brothers Shine in FA Youth Cup as Scotland Fans Hope for The Best|first=Harry|last=Gillies|date=March 2, 2025|work=Sports Gazette}}</ref>

